<br>
Now you can visit www.microsoft.com in the search field type: <br>
<br>
Application Compatibility Toolkit XP <br>
<br>
click on the FIRST link that comes up <br>
<br>
download act26.exe <br>
<br>
install the program you just downloaded from <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>MICROSOFT </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
under applications, scroll down to Everquest <br>
<br>
go the right hand pane (window) <br>
<br>
disable the entry that discusses alt+tab being disabled <br>
<br>
Little researched fact that it breaks <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Microsofts EULA</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to for any Windows based software to interfere with the Windows multi-tasking functions....including altering the ability to Alt-Tab between open applications. Microsoft offers this little DL which will stop any app from blocking ALT-TAB, including EQ. When posted to VI's boards, they jumped all over it and closed discussion as you can see in the above quoted link.<br>
<br>
You can also use EQWindows which allows you to Alt-Tab as it forces EQ to run in Windowed Mode.  You can get EQW at:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqwindows.com">www.eqwindows.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
